# Production Environment Variables Template

## Required Variables (NO DEFAULTS - Must be set)

# PostgreSQL for Abada Engine
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=<strong-password-here>

# Keycloak Admin
KEYCLOAK_ADMIN_USERNAME=<admin-username>
KEYCLOAK_ADMIN_PASSWORD=<strong-admin-password>

# Keycloak Database
KEYCLOAK_DB_PASSWORD=<strong-db-password>

# Keycloak Hostname (e.g., auth.abada.dev)
KEYCLOAK_HOSTNAME=<your-keycloak-domain>

# Application Hostname (e.g., app.abada.dev)
APP_HOSTNAME=<your-app-domain>

# OAuth2 Proxy
OAUTH2_PROXY_CLIENT_ID=abada-frontend-prod
OAUTH2_PROXY_CLIENT_SECRET=<generate-strong-secret>
# Generate with: openssl rand -base64 32
OAUTH2_PROXY_COOKIE_SECRET=<32-random-characters>

## Optional Variables (Have defaults)

# Abada Engine Replicas (default: 3)
ABADA_ENGINE_REPLICAS=3

# Grafana Admin Password (default: admin - CHANGE THIS!)
GRAFANA_ADMIN_PASSWORD=<grafana-admin-password>

## Security Notes

1. **NEVER commit `.env` files to version control**
2. Use a secrets manager (Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, etc.) in production
3. Rotate secrets regularly
4. Use strong, unique passwords for each service
5. Generate OAUTH2_PROXY_COOKIE_SECRET with: `openssl rand -base64 32 | tr -d '/+='  | head -c 32`
